Update Frappe apps to their latest versions.

By default, updates all apps. Specify app names to update specific apps.
This pulls the latest code, updates dependencies, and rebuilds assets.

Examples:
  weg update              # Update all apps
  weg update frappe       # Update only frappe
  weg update --pull       # Only pull, skip dependency install
  weg update --no-build   # Skip asset rebuild

To upgrade Frappe to the next major version, see 'weg upgrade'.
To update weg itself, see 'weg self update'.

Usage:
  weg update [app...] [flags]

Flags:
  -h, --help       help for update
      --no-build   Skip asset rebuild after update
      --no-deps    Skip dependency installation
      --pull       Only pull latest code, skip dependency install

Global Flags:
  -C, --chdir string              Run as if weg was started in <path>
      --config string             Path to config file (default: auto-detect)
      --debug-categories string   Filter debug output: all,config,state,net,git,fs,exec
      --log-level string          Set log level: quiet, normal, verbose, debug, trace
  -o, --output string             Output format: auto, json, table, plain, quiet (default "auto")
  -q, --quiet                     Suppress non-essential output
  -v, --verbose count             Increase verbosity (-v, -vv, -vvv)
  -y, --yes                       Assume yes for all prompts
